 alt="The Great Departure"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;Having decided to embark on the spiritual path, Siddhartha cuts his hair, removes his royal garments, and puts on rag robes. Illustration from Life of the Buddha, Burmese Edition, via The Jade Turtle Records.&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h2 id="preface"&gt;Preface&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This poem was written during my second Traditional Rain Retreat. It is a reflection meant to generate the mind of &amp;ldquo;renunciation&amp;rdquo;, although the correct word to convey the meaning of the sanskrit words niḥsaraṇa or niryāṇa would be &amp;ldquo;emergence&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;going forth&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>